dictionary.description: "Silent and solemn Osiris, the first god of the ancient pantheon, was initially the patron of fertility and earthly abundance. Years of bitter conflict with a jealous sibling culminated in his untimely death, but it was his devoted wife Aesys who purified his mangled flesh with flame. Thus was Osiris reborn and interred as the sovereign of the netherworld Duat, mirroring the natural cycle of nature.
dictionary.evolution:
Long the rivers of the Duat flowed,
but now they are sunken dregs of misery and suffering.
Aesys, my dearest...I hope you are safe.
dictionary.fusion:
What use are such offerings
when I am no longer worthy of them?
Do you still hold reverence for a felled god, mortal?
dictionary.summon:
Mortal. Hear me.
I am a hollowed shell of a god, and yet you persist in calling upon me...
What good can come of it?
